# =========================================================================
# This file tells Git which files and folders to ignore.
# It is a critical security feature to prevent secrets from being uploaded.
# =========================================================================

# Node.js dependencies
# These folders contain thousands of files that can be re-downloaded
# using `npm install`. They should never be committed.
node_modules/
/client/node_modules/
/Server/node_modules/

# Environment secrets file
# This is the MOST IMPORTANT line. It prevents your secret API keys
# for MongoDB, SendGrid, Cloudinary, etc., from being uploaded.
Server/.env

# Log files
# Ignore any log files that might be generated.
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# System files
# Ignore operating system-specific files.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
```

After you have saved this file in the correct location, you will need to commit it to your repository.

```bash
git add .gitignore
git commit -m "Feat: Create a comprehensive .gitignore file"
git push

